**Must read if there is any doubt feel free to ask in comments**

Somehow beginners face difficulty to understand the concept at first, but i will try my best to breakdown the question into simpler parts so that there would be ease to understand for beginners.



**first we have to check prime number on the diagnol of the matrix.**

**Step 1** -> so we make a function to check wether the given number is prime or not

**Note** -> there are several functions to checkPrime as a naive/beginner you apply what you have learnt in fundamentals programming but it would not work

But here we have to create a checkPrime no. function that would be  optimized otherwise you will get **TLE** which is **Time Limit Exceeded** error.


To find a prime number what we do firstly? -> find factors

e.g
 Num - > 12
factors -> 

    **i** -------- **k**
    1 * 12 = 12
    2 * 6 = 12
    3 * 4 = 12
    4 * 3 = 12
    6 * 2 = 12
    12 * 1 = 12

we have total 6 factors 

**Trivial method: TLE occurs for this coz it isn't optimized.**

int count = 0;
if (k < 2) {
    return false;
}
for (int i = 1; i < k; i++) {
    if (k % i == 0) {
        count++;        
    }
}
if (count == 2) {
    return true;
} else {
    return false;
}

Now what if I say we do not need to iterate till k if we focus on the pattern we see that after i = 3 same numbers are repeating such as (4,3) despite (3,4) was there already , similarly (6,2) despite (2,6) is there etc...

now what we do is we would iterate our loop from **i to √k** or we can write it as **i * i to k** also **so that our i iterate in the range between [1 - 3] so we have to take the square root of k. 
i.e 
1 * 12, 2 * 6, 3 * 4 and we get all the 6 factors till i = 3.**


e.g
 Num - > 12
factors -> 1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 12
**i ------- k**
1 * 12 = 12
2 * 6 = 12
3 * 4 = 12

 4 * 3 = 12
 6 * 2 = 12
12 * 1 = 12

for (int i = 1; i * i <= k; i++) {
    if (k < 2) {
    return false;
    }
    if (k % i == 0) {
        count +=2; 
//count + 2 because 1 * 12 we grab two factors from herethen why we need to go till 12.

}
if (count == 2) {
return true
} else {
return false;
}
}

**Now we have converted our problem in √n time complexity.**







